    <content type="html"><![CDATA[<h1 id="Introduction"><a href="#Introduction" class="headerlink" title="Introduction"></a>Introduction</h1><p>This extension adds more functions to game camera, such as manipulate camera for each layer (backgrounds, pictures or characters) instead of the whole screen.</p><blockquote><ul><li>Requires <a href="http://vnm.yami.moe/2017/11/17/core-engine">Core Engine</a>.</li></ul></blockquote><h1 id="Download-amp-Install"><a href="#Download-amp-Install" class="headerlink" title="Download &amp; Install"></a>Download &amp; Install</h1><p><a href="https://drive.google.com/open?id=1xE9to6CLY4O2nPPToxPPy4Pdf3oBQXm2" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Download</a></p><p>Use <code>Extension Manager</code> to install the zip file.</p><h1 id="How-to-use"><a href="#How-to-use" class="headerlink" title="How to use"></a>How to use</h1><h2 id="Added-Commands"><a href="#Added-Commands" class="headerlink" title="Added Commands"></a>Added Commands</h2><p>Those commands are added into Scene Commands List.<br><figure class="highlight plain"><table><tr><td class="gutter"><pre><span class="line">1</span><br><span class="line">2</span><br><span class="line">3</span><br><span class="line">4</span><br><span class="line">5</span><br></pre></td><td class="code"><pre><span class="line">Screen</span><br><span class="line">  | Camera</span><br><span class="line">    &gt; Pan Layer</span><br><span class="line">    &gt; Zoom Layer</span><br><span class="line">    &gt; Rotate Layer</span><br></pre></td></tr></table></figure></p><h1 id="Version"><a href="#Version" class="headerlink" title="Version"></a>Version</h1><h2 id="v1-0-0-0-2017-11-17"><a href="#v1-0-0-0-2017-11-17" class="headerlink" title="v1.0.0.0 (2017 - 11 - 17)"></a>v1.0.0.0 (2017 - 11 - 17)</h2><ul><li>First Release.</li></ul>]]></content>
    
